    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. looking at the dataset for the litigation, some of the automated flags seem a bit... odd. they're flagging things that aren't strictly material under the standard def, but they seem to be looking for these very subtle, almost weird subtextual links. can you explain why the logic might be prioritizing those nuances over a literal reading of the text?",
