      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you on the \"exhaustive exploration,\" but the client isn't paying for an \"overload of non-matters.\" It's actually slowing down our review process and costing too much. I'm thinking about adjusting your configuration to tighten up the parameters—basically, I want to prune those extra \"subtle indicators\" and force the model to stick to a much more literal, strict interpretation of materiality to save time. do you see any issues with narrowing the focus like that?",
